==English==
===Etymology===
English colre, from Old French, from Latin cholera, cholera, jaundice, from Greek kholera, from khol, bile

===Pronunciation===
kol'eric or kol-er'ic

===Adjective===
# Being easily [[angered]] or [[bad-tempered]].
# Showing or expressing [[anger]].


